description: For sale: $250,000. Wonderful, 4 bedroom, 2 bath rambler located in the Valley Place neighborhood! 3 nice sized bedrooms on one level! Eat-in kitchen! Formal dining area with built-in hutch! Original hard wood floors in hallway and bedrooms. Easy care wood laminate flooring in living room and dining area! Huge lower level family room for entertaining and play, includes a large built-in bar! Plenty of space for pool table or game tables! Built-in entertainment center includes desk/work station, built-in bench with hidden storage and cubbies to display your toys! Exceptional, stone patio runs the entire length of the home! A perfect place to enjoy our Minnesota summers around the fire! Large garden behind the garage, a compost bin and a garden/storage shed to keep all the tools! City bus stop on the corner of 32nd and Louisiana! Valley Place Community Park includes: Baseball & soccer fields, basketball and tennis courts, hockey & skating rinks with a warming house, a sliding hill and covered picnic area!

For sale: $310,000. Wonderful opportunity in South Crystal. This move-in ready home features a huge, sunny fenced in yard, hardwood floors & bonus main level family room with gas fireplace and entertainment center. Many tasteful updates including remodeled bathrooms, stainless appliances, and newer windows throughout for tons of natural light. Convenient location near schools and parks. Must see!

description: For sale: $329,900. Welcome to 3025 Cavell Avenue North.  This charming 3-bedroom 3-bathroom two-story in a highly desirable New Hope neighborhood could be your next home!  The living room is warm and inviting with gleaming hardwood floors and large picture windows.  The kitchen opens to the dining room, making it ideal to visit with family and friends while preparing meals and entertaining.  The three bedrooms on the upper level all have hardwood floors and lots of closet space.  The master suite has a beautifully tiled 3/4 master bath.  The lower level features an exercise room and family room with a working area perfect for getting things completed.  The home offers lots of storage in the utility and laundry room.  The spectacular backyard features a concrete patio, mature trees, and a spacious flat yard - you will love spending your summers in this yard!  This home has been beautifully updated with fresh paint and is meticulously maintained.

For sale: $350,000. Classic mid-century styling updated for today's busy lifestyles. Gorgeous stainless kitchen with hard surface counter tops and abundant cabinetry.  Open living space with 3/4" hardwood through majority of main floor. Open dining/living lays across the back of the main floor and boast a wall of windows overlooking the 1/3 acre, private yard. 3 generous bedrooms up and a 4th guest bedroom down offer flexibilty. floor to ceiling fireplaces in Living Room and huge lower level family room.  Loads of storage including a cedar closet in the basement, large indoor storage room and outdoor shop or storage space under the garage.  Amazing location, walkable to downtown Golden Valley and 10 minutes from downtown Minneapolis.

3 bedrooms on the main level have exposed hardwood floors.  The lower level was recently refinished with a huge family room and an updated 3/4 bath.  There is space to add a 4th bedroom and still have a large family room. Detached, one-car garage, cement driveway.  Both house and garage have steel siding. The big yard has mature trees yet plenty of sun of you are a gardener.  Low maintenance landscaping around the home allow for carefree weekends and summers.  Quick access to Hwy 169 and is also on the bus line.  Near Medley Hills Park, General Mills campus and 20-25 minutes to downtown Minneapolis and all it has to offer.

description: Recently sold: $315,000. Mid-century Modern split level home with 4br upstairs and original kitchen cabinets, oven and Redwood siding. description:
Recently sold: $300,000. Wonderful double bungalow duplex income property opportunity in New Hope! Eat-in kitchens have been updated with new cabinets, counter-tops, backsplashes, stainless steel appliances and luxury vinyl tile floors. Each side has beautifully refinished original hardwood floors, two bedrooms and a full bath that has been updated with new vanities, lighting and ceramic tile surrounds. Basements are newly partially finished with one unit having a third finished bedroom and 3/4 bath and the other unit having a finished family room. Each unit has a parking spot in a detached two-car-garage with plenty of off-street parking. Close to city bus and Minneapolis.

INTERESTED BUYERS: call us at (612) 405-3009 for a private showing or email us at emilie@kerbyandcristina.com. 
 
AGENT INQUIRIES: please request more info or a showing via email only at emilie@kerbyandcristina.com.

Recently sold: $269,000. Come see this hard to find Golden Valley gem in Hopkins School District, that is priced to sell. There is a fully remodeled basement entertainment area, which includes a wet bar. Property is professionally landscaped, with a large deck and patio, a 6x12' shed, and a six foot high privacy fence. description: Recently sold: $342,500. Natural light flows throughout this wonderful family home in a great Golden Valley neighborhood! There's plenty of room in this 4 bedroom, 2 bath rambler, with an open living room and dining room space that is perfect for entertaining or family nights at home! There's a great lower level family room that walks out to a generous, fully fenced-in yard (the play set can stay!). You'll love the recently renovated bathrooms, beautiful hardwood floors, all the nice-sized closets, and the huge storage room! The 4th bedroom is currently non-conforming, but the sellers will have the egress window installed before closing. Close to everything - Shopping and Restaurants, Parks and Schools, Brookview and Golden Valley Country Club - and just minutes to downtown Minneapolis! You won't want to miss this wonderful home!

Recently sold: $196,000. Beautiful twin-home available for rent on 4/1/2014! Two bedroom, 1.5 bathrooms and attached 2 stall garage. Nice size patio, fireplace, new appliances, new laundry, new furnace/ac, recently renovated, hardwoods in lower level, carpeted upper level, association perks (free lawn/snow care and outdoor pool access), walking path adjacent to property, and quick access to schools, highways, and shopping. You will love this beautiful home that is ready to rent on March 1st, 2014. Please call or email Ken at kproulx@yahoo.com or 612-998-6181! 

Rental Features
 - Cable ready
 - Microwave
 - Air conditioning
 - Refrigerator
 - Dishwasher
 - Patio
 - Garage parking
 - Laundry
 - Fireplace
 - Oven / range
 - Heat - high efficiency gas

Property Features
 - Pool

Lease Terms $1,250.00 rent plus one month security deposit, 12 months or longer lease term. $35 app fee per adult and $35 per cosigner (if applicable). This property is NOT section 8 approved. Tenants are responsible for all utilities. No pets and no smoking.

Recently sold: $145,000. Absolutely impeccable and completely updated 2 bedroom 2 bath upper level corner unit in an ultra secure New Hope condominium building. The super spacious and vaulted open floor plan is drenched in natural light from east and north facing exposure! Brand new kitchen in 2017 features modern quartz counters, all new white shaker cabinetry and stainless appliances including a huge walk-in pantry with newer washer/dryer and built-in shelving. New Pergo wood flooring in living/dining and bedrooms in 2012, two new wall AC units in 2011. New roof and maintenance-free vinyl siding in 2009. This home has been lovingly cared for and shows like new! Excellent owner's suite with full bath and private deck. Conveniently located just off Hwy 169 with easy access to grocery stores, retail, restaurants and bus line directly out your front door. A true treasure!

Recently sold: $228,000. Solid, mid-century rambler with 3 bedrooms on one level, fully-fenced back yard, perennial flowers and nice location, close to parks, shops & easy access to nearby highways. Homes has a nice-sized two stall attached garage, screened in 3 season porch, 10x 12 shed, and also a 19 x 12 workshop in basement. Newer mechanicals, roof and Andersen windows. Oak hardwood floors underneath carpet. Well-cared for home by the same owners since 1972, in a central location and awaits your personal touches.

description:
Recently sold: $315,000. Prime Location!! Close to shopping, restaurants, parks, and more! Charming side-by-side duplex in a safe and friendly neighborhood. Near HW 100 providing easy access to Downtown, Uptown, West End and other major roadways. Enter from your spacious front deck into a large living space which flows into the updated kitchen with new counters, stainless steel apliances, and ample storage. At the back of the house you'll find a full bath and 2 bedrooms. There is an additional bedroom and renovated 3/4 bath in the basement. Enjoy hardwood floors, central air, separate washer and dryer, detached garage option for an additional fee, and plenty of off-street parking. Last but not least this home has a large fenced-in backyard and is pet-friendly for friendly pets! Come join us for an open house 9/1/19 from 10:00am to 1:00pm! Sorry, no section 8.

description: Recently sold: $665,000. Thoughtfully designed in partnership w/architect, Ben Nelson, this beautiful home provides a private setting, nestled by nature and mature trees, just fifteen minutes from downtown Mpls.  Perfect for entertaining, w/a relaxed and open floor plan, the owners easily entertain 60 people at a time. The kitchen features Birch floors, Northland custom cherry cabinetry, granite countertops, KitchenAid appliances and walk-in pantry.  The beautiful woodwork extends throughout the home into the Great Room where you'll find cherry built-in bookcases surrounding a sunny reading nook and wall to wall bookcases surrounding the gas fireplace. The screen porch is a perfect place to enjoy warm weather. It opens to perennial gardens and flagstone patio w/firepit. The 2nd floor features a peaceful master suite and bath w/ large shower and granite topped double vanity; laundry and 2 guest bedrooms. The lower level offers heated cement floors, a family room that could be an office or exercise room and a bedroom and  bath.

Recently sold: $303,752. Wonderfully updated walk-out rambler with tons of garage space. Located in prestigious Hopkins school district of Golden Valley and just steps to a beautiful public park. Access to both public transit and freeways (169) are within one block of residence. 

Walk into your new home and through the renovated kitchen out onto your observation deck above a 24' x 24' detached garage. Your fenced in yard has plenty of room for your family pet to enjoy And features a unique corral suitable for a recreational RV, boat or trailer.

Walk downstairs to your new living room with ample built in storage, updated 3/4 bathroom and access to your 1.5 car tuck under insulated garage. The insulated detached garage is more than enough space for 2 cars with room to spare.

Galley kitchen on main level includes ample storage and prep area including small breakfast counter. Carbonized bamboo hardwood flooring leads you through the living room to your 3 bedrooms and full bath. Spare bedroom was used as an office with built in queen Murphy bed ready for guests.

This home was COMPLETLEY renovated in 2009 with the basement undergoing another transformation to its current layout in 2013. The common area flooring from the kitchen to the bedroom hallway was replaced with ultra hard carbonized bamboo hardwoods in 2014. Many lighting fixtures including whisper quick fans installed throughout the main level and bedrooms.

description: Recently sold: $113,000. This beautiful updated 2 bedroom 1 bath unit is perfect for those looking for convenient living. This renovated unit is nestled between several parks (including Medicine Lake), Golden Valley Golf Course/Brookview Golf Course/Minneapolis Golf Course and downtown Minneapolis-a mere 8 miles away by car or take the bus- the busline is within a 1/2 block of the building. The property also offers a modern kitchen including stainless steel appliances, natural stone tile backsplash accented by under cabinet lighting, movable island with butcher-block top, corner bench seating and a breakfast table with storage. Other amenities include mirrored closet doors, stacked full size laundry in-unit, air conditioning, ceiling fan and full window treatments. For storage, there are lighted closets in each room featuring premium closet organizer systems, a linen closet and a 7x4 walk in closet with adjustable wooden shelves. The included enclosed garage comes with finished and painted walls, built-in workbench and shelves, attic storage and added lighting--a real handyman's workshop! There is also an electric garage door opener w/ transmitter for your convenience. For safety, the building houses a secure entryway and intercom system along with ample lighting. Mail is on premisis too. When you add it up, this unit offers you exceptional value, low-cost living and modern conveniences while living only minutes away from the heart of Minneapolis.Rental term is a minimum of 12 months with the option to buy in the future. Heat, water, garbage and all exterior maintenanceis INCLUDED in rent . Dog and cats are ok with association limitations on size and number (pet deposit required). Application fee applies, but credited to first month's rent if approved. Please no UD's, felonies or derogatory rental history. Income verification required as well.

description:
Recently sold: $300,000. Main Level
* Welcoming foyer with gleaming hardwood floors that flow from foyer to dinette, kitchen and bedrooms.
* Upgrades galore throughout entire home!
* Vibrant vaulted living room with wall-of-windows for abundant natural light.  Easy deck access.
* Kitchen features stainless steel appliances, Silestone countertops, tile backsplash, wine rack and stem rack, mug hooks, pass through window to living room, designer lights with under cabinet lighting. 
* Adjacent dinette offers open floor plan perfect for entertaining and easy garage access.
* Spacious master bedroom.
* 3 bedrooms on one level.  Closets with custom clothes racking. 
* Full bath with tile floor, tile surround soaking tub, tile shower, double sink vanity, stylish towel hooks and window.
Lower Level
* Large family room offers recessed lighting, pendant lighting, re-purposed bowling lane bar, additional built-in bar with shelves and cabinets.  
* Unfinished clean storage area perfect for workshop or place for all your extras.
* 3/4 bath with tile floor, tile walk-in shower and vessel sink.
* Laundry room with washer and dryer included.
Additional 
* 2010 - Roof and drain tile.  Remodel main level bath.
* 2011 - Doors, window, siding/soffit/facia.
* 2015 - Main level deck with quality privacy wall.  Remodel lower level bath.
* 2016 - Concrete sidewalk.  All new kitchen.
* 2017- New sewer line to main.
All information deemed reliable but not guaranteed.

description:
Recently sold: $83,000. Available Now! Move-in Special: Move in between June 1st-June 15th and get two weeks free! Come see this wonderful one bedroom, one bathroom condo. Notice a spacious living room with plenty of natural light from generous windows. Included in this room are a large coat closet with lots of space for extra storage, and a stacked, in-unit washer dryer. Continue on to find the kitchen and dining space with a convenient ceiling fan. Next is the bathroom with a bathtub and brightly lit vanity. Down the hall is the bedroom with a great deal of natural light and spacious closets. This unit is located in New Hope, Minnesota. There is a delightful and grassy park accessible right behind this building. There are also many options for dining and entertainment within close proximity. Can't wait to make this condo your future home? Give us a call or send an email!

Amazingly convenient location about 15 minutes to DT Minneapolis, most shopping within 5-10 minutes or less including West End, Ridgedale, etc.  Easy access to Hwy 169 & 394.    Well-maintained pool just a few steps away!  Oversized 2-car garage, lots of storage, huge deck out front, patio access with large yard in back. Rent includes trash removal, snow removal, & meticulous yard maintenance with care-free lifestyle.

1. A 12-month lease is currently being offered, with ability to renew longer-term.
2. An application fee of $45 per adult is due at time of application for background and credit check.
3. Security deposit of $1880, with an additional $250 non-refundable pet deposit for cats/small dogs. Please note that dogs should be non-aggressive breed and under 40 lbs. 
4. Please answer the following questions below prior to requesting a showing:

-Reason for moving
-Number of tenants applying to live at property
-Gross household monthly income should be 3x monthly rent
-A minimum requirement of 600 FICO score and no evictions/criminal history
-Sorry this property is not approved for Section 8
